        <body>
            <div type="edition" subtype="primary" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="la" resp="#JP">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan></supplied> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan> <g ref="#ivy-leaf">❦</g> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>acrum</ex></expan>
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><persName type="attested"><name><w part="F">nta</w></name> <g ref="#interpunct">·</g> <name><w part="I">Fla</w></name></persName>
                     <lb n="3" break="no"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <g ref="#interpunct">·</g> vixit <g ref="#interpunct">·</g> 
                     <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">an</supplied>nis <g ref="#interpunct">·</g> <num value="18">XVIII</num>
                    <lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost">p</supplied><unclear>a</unclear>ter fecit
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text from autopsy/photograph</note></app>
                    <app loc="5"><note>Alternatively: [m]ater; the serif of the foot of the initial A is just visible.</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#JP">
                <p>Sacro agli dei Mani. [---]nta Fla[---] visse 18 anni. Il padre (o la madre) fece.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Sacred to the shades of the underworld. [---]nta Fla[---] lived 18 years. Her father (or mother) made it.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The first, fourth and fifth lines indicate that only 2-3 letters are missing on the left side, suggesting a pair of names such as Quinta Flavia (but many other names such as Amynta, Inventa, Leonta, etc. are also possible).</p>
            </div>
